Reasoning: The paper deals with wireless communication systems and specifically focuses on the Diversity-Multiplexing gain Trade-off (DMT) of a training based reciprocal Single Input Multiple Output (SIMO) system. This falls under the domain of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communication (cs.COMM). The paper also proposes a channel-dependent fixed-power training scheme and a forward-link data transmit power control scheme, which involves system optimization and control, falling under the domains of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper uses Monte Carlo simulations to illustrate the outage performance of the proposed scheme, which falls under the domain of Multimedia (cs.MM).
